    {
      "meta": {
        "name": "Tetraspeck",
        "shortDescription": "Tetraspeck",
        "description": "This pipeline steps enables the removal of calibration beads (e.g. tetraspeck) that are fluorescent in all channels. \n1. Enable pipeline \ud83d\udc41\n2. Select Tetraspeck image channel (channel showing only tetraspecks)\n3. Adapt (manual) threshold \n4. Within the *Reclassify* command select the channels where tetraspeck need to be removed. Approximation notes: $reclassify was approximated via Colocalization",
        "authorFirstName": "EVAnalyzer",
        "authorLastName": "Team",
        "authorOrganization": "evanalyzer.org",
        "creationTime": "2026-06-11T00:00:00Z"
      },
      "pipelineSteps": [
