    {
      "meta": {
        "name": "Coloc ",
        "shortDescription": "Coloc ",
        "description": "Colocalisation is set to 0.1 (0.1-1) as default and may be changed.\n\nWith these settings you will find the following groups:\nall spots: includes coloc and non-coloc spots\n- non colocalising ch1, ch2, ch3: spots only detected in the one respective channel\n- 2 channel coloc spots: e.g. ch1and 2 includes all spots that have channel 1 and 2 and also includes spots that might have ch3\n- 3 channel coloc spots: spots recognized in ch1, 2 and 3\n Approximation notes: $reclassify was approximated via Colocalization $reclassify was approximated via Colocalization $reclassify was approximated via Colocalization $colocalization N-way matrix approximated as pairwise Colocalization steps (each non-Undefined entry paired with the first other non-Undefined entry) $colocalization N-way matrix approximated as pairwise Colocalization steps (each non-Undefined entry paired with the first other non-Undefined entry) $colocalization N-way matrix approximated as pairwise Colocalization steps (each non-Undefined entry paired with the first other non-Undefined entry) $colocalization N-way matrix approximated as pairwise Colocalization steps (each non-Undefined entry paired with the first other non-Undefined entry)",
        "authorFirstName": "EVAnalyzer",
        "authorLastName": "Team",
        "authorOrganization": "evanalyzer.org",
        "creationTime": "2026-06-11T00:00:00Z"
      },
      "pipelineSteps": [
